%N A395810 Decimal expansion of the real solution of the equation 2*x^3 - 2*x^2 + 2*x - 1 = 0.
%C A395810 This constant gives the value of the ratio between the length of the smaller cathetus and that of the greater cathetus of a right-angled triangle having the sum of the length of the height relative to the hypotenuse and that of the smaller cathetus equal to the length of the hypotenuse.
%C A395810 Equivalently, the real solution of the equation x + 1/sqrt(1 + (1/x)^2) = sqrt(1 + x^2).
%D A395810 John Derbyshire, Unknown Quantity: A Real and Imaginary History of Algebra. Washington, DC: Joseph Henry Press (2006): 55.
%H A395810 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_03">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 3</a>.
%F A395810 Equals (1 - 2^(5/3)/(13 + 3*sqrt(33))^(1/3) + (13 + 3*sqrt(33))^(1/3)/2^(2/3))/3.
%F A395810 Equals (2 - 2^(8/3)/(13 + 3*sqrt(33))^(1/3) + (26 + 6*sqrt(33))^(1/3))/6.
%F A395810 Equals 1/A256099.
%F A395810 Equals sqrt(A380775 - 1). - _Hugo Pfoertner_, May 07 2026
%e A395810 0.64779887126104238549049829642576930694948772422...
%t A395810 RealDigits[First[SolveValues[2#^3-2#^2+2#-1==0,#]],10,100][[1]]
%o A395810 (PARI) (2 - 2^(8/3)/(13 + 3*sqrt(33))^(1/3) + (26 + 6*sqrt(33))^(1/3))/6
